Former Orlando Pirates and Kaizer Chiefs goalkeeper Brilliant Khuzwayo has survived an alleged stabbing incident. Khuzwayo was attending a sport event as a guest speaker at the Mangosuthu University of Technology (MUT) on Saturday when the incident happened. The perpetrator is believed to be a student at the institution. Khuzwayo was rushed to the hospital and a case was opened with the Umlazi SAPS. “17-10-2020 Brilliant Khuzwayo was invited to speak at the Mangosuthu University of Technology (MUT) sports event. Right before he could make his address, a male believed to be a MUT student stabbed him and he was rushed to the hospital. A case has since been opened with Umlazi SAPS," read a tweet sent through Khuzwayo’s official Twitter account. 17-10-2020 Brilliant Khuzwayo was invited to speak at the Mangosuthu University of Technology (MUT) sports event. Right before he could make his address, a male believed to be a MUT student stabbed him and he was rushed to the hospital.A case has been opened with Umlazi SAPS. pic.twitter.com/kxaehxfvHR 